ce:section.ce:para:
In Fig. 12
                      we are presenting the calculated energy spectrum in twisted bilayer GQDs with circular geometry. The corresponding dot sizes and twisting angles are represented for pairs of nearest (m, n) as defined above (see Table 1
                     ). The evolution from smaller size-angle to larger values of these quantities shows a reduction of the energy band gap which goes from 1.86 eV for (2, 1) to ∼0.108 eV for (6, 1). In particular, Fig. 12(b) shows the spectra corresponding to commensurate ratios of pairs (m, n), and the same tendency of reduction of the energy band gap appears.
